BinomialModelSimulator - Class in com.andreamazzon.session4.composition.binomialmodel
This class is used in order to simulate some oaths of a binomial model: discrete model for a stochastic process S, such that every time i we have S(i+1)=S(i)*M(i), where M(i)=u>1 with probability p and M(i)=d<1 with probability 1-p.
BinomialModelSimulator - Class in com.andreamazzon.session5.abstractclasses.simulators
This class is used in order to simulate some paths of a binomial model: discrete model for a stochastic process S, such that every time i we have S(i+1)=S(i)*M(i), where M(i)=u>1 with probability p and M(i)=d<1 with probability 1-p.

BinomialModelUser - Class in com.andreamazzon.session4.composition.binomialmodel
This class has methods to get the paths, the simulated value at a given time and the average value at given time of a binomial model: discrete model for a stochastic process S, such that every time i we have S(i+1)=S(i)*M(i), where M(i)=u>1 with probability p and M(i)=d<1 with probability 1-p.
BinomialModelUser - Class in com.andreamazzon.session5.abstractclasses.usingsimulators
This class inherits from StochasticProcessUser, which provides methods to get the paths, the simulated value at a given time and the average value at given time of a general stochastic process.
